================================================================================
                    DEBUGGING ROUND - OFFICIAL INSTRUCTIONS
================================================================================

  Time Limit  : 30 Minutes
  Problems    : 3  (P1, P2, P3)
  Points Each : 5
  Total Marks : 15

  Read every rule carefully before you begin.

================================================================================
  LANGUAGE
================================================================================

  1. You must work in ONE of the following languages:
                        C++  |  Java  |  Python

  2. You MAY switch languages mid-round. However:
       - The 30-minute timer does NOT stop or reset.
       - Time spent on your previous language is gone.
       - You must submit the complete set of files for your FINAL language.
       - Switching is entirely at your own risk.

  3. All three languages are equally difficult. Choose what you know best.

================================================================================
  SCORING
================================================================================

  - Each problem is worth 5 points.
  - Full marks are awarded ONLY if the program produces correct output
    for ALL test cases. There are no partial marks within a problem.
  - Problems are scored independently.

================================================================================
  RULES
================================================================================

  1. FIX, DON'T REWRITE
     You must fix the given code. You may NOT rewrite it from scratch
     or replace the existing logic with a different approach.
     The original algorithm must remain intact.

  2. NO NEW BUILT-IN FUNCTIONS OR LIBRARIES
     You may only use built-in functions or library calls that are
     ALREADY present in the original buggy code.
     Adding new ones to solve the problem is not allowed.
     This rule applies equally to all languages -- no exceptions.
     Standard input/output functions are always permitted.

  3. NO ALTERNATIVE ALGORITHMS
     The algorithm used in each program is fixed. You must debug that
     specific algorithm. Replacing it with any other approach -- even
     one that gives the correct output -- will result in zero for
     that problem.

================================================================================
  SUBMISSIONS
================================================================================

  - Submit all 3 files for your chosen language before the timer ends.
  - Only your last submission per problem will be evaluated.
  - Ensure your code compiles and runs without errors before submitting.

================================================================================
  PROHIBITED CONDUCT
================================================================================

  The following will result in immediate disqualification:

    - Communicating with any other participant.
    - Using AI tools or code assistants of any kind.
    - Using online compilers that suggest or auto-correct code.
    - Sharing or copying code.
    - Mobile phones or smartwatches during the round.

================================================================================
  PROBLEMS
================================================================================

  Details for each problem are in the following files:

    P1 -- p1.txt   (Vowel Counter)
    P2 -- p2.txt   (Binary Search)
    P3 -- p3.txt   (Fibonacci + Factorial Challenge)

  Read the problem file for your task, expected input/output format,
  and examples before looking at the code.

================================================================================
  If you have any questions, raise your hand and wait for an invigilator.
              Good luck -- read carefully, and think before you change.
================================================================================